The study will examine the challenges associated with the existing process of banks to identify deceased accounts and take necessary action. The project will propose an process that enables faster identification of deceased customers through better information database and integration of AI and technology with the existing system. 
However scope of this study does not include the detailed legal procedures related to inheritance or final account settlement. It also does not suggest the steps to be taken for establishing legal frameworks regarding data privacy. The study includes the requirement only for individual accounts and not for accounts such as HUF or partnership firms.
